OKPEKPE – Expectedly, the Ethiopians swept the stakes at the eight Okpekpe International 10km Road Race in Okpekpe on Saturday. The men’s elite category was won by Jason Hadi, who returned a time of 29.05 minutes, winning $13,000. Kenyan Elvis Cheboi returned 15seconds later to win silver and $8,000 the prize money. Bereket Nego, another Ethiopian was third in 29:30minutes and $5,000 prize money.The story was also not different in the women’s elites -Advertisement- Class as Ethiopian athlete won gold in 33.09minutes, while Kenyans won the silver and bronze. Anchinain Dessie won the gold with the duo of Dorcas Kimeli (33:33) and Abigael Mutai (33:53) winning silver and bronze respectively.The winning prize for both sexes are the same. In the Nigerian class, Ismael Sadiq returned a time of 31:12 minutes to win gold and N500,000.00 with Adamu Muazu placing second in 31:15minutes and N300,000 prize money with Emmanuel Gyang third in 31:32 minutes to win bronze and N200,000.00 prize money. Rose Akuahe won the Nigerian elite class in 36:40 minutes with Abiye Joy (37:59) and Patience Datylop(38:07) winning silver and bronze respectively. The women also got the same prize money as the men.